<subSubSection id="E1CB653A9902803E4AD55B4CFEF861C0" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A96E36B19902803E4AD55B4CFEF861C0" blockId="15.[101,1032,443,1493]" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">
Comments. 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D329902803E4B5C5B4CFD956130" authorityName="Jocélia Grazia" authorityYear="2003" box="[300,535,1294,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schuhi">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA39902803E4B5C5B4CFD956130" box="[300,535,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">Brachystethus schuhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares with its sister species 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D329902803E491B5B4CFC5E6130" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[875,988,1294,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribrus">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA39902803E491B5B4CFC5E6130" box="[875,988,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">B. cribrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the yellowish callus on corium, but can be distinguished by the following characters: venter uniformly castaneous, dark-castaneous coxae and genital cup processes moderately visible dorsally. 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D329902803E4B505B24FD886168" authorityName="Jocélia Grazia" authorityYear="2003" box="[288,522,1382,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schuhi">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA39902803E4B505B24FD886168" box="[288,522,1382,1405]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">Brachystethus schuhi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D329902803E49435B24FC366168" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1872" box="[819,948,1382,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signoreti">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA39902803E49435B24FC366168" box="[819,948,1382,1405]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">B. signoreti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D329902803E49805B24FE8C618F" authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubromaculatus">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA39902803E49805B24FE8C618F" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="428">B. rubromaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CD404B409902803E4B6B5BC1FDB9618F" author="BARCELLOS, A. &amp; GRAZIA, J." box="[283,571,1411,1434]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa, Auckland" pageId="15" pageNumber="428" pagination="1 - 14" part="256" refId="ref19723" refString="BARCELLOS, A. &amp; GRAZIA, J. 2003. Cladistic analysis and biogeography of Brachystethus Laporte (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae, Edessinae). Zootaxa, Auckland, 256: 1 - 14." title="Cladistic analysis and biogeography of Brachystethus Laporte (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae, Edessinae)" type="journal article" year="2003">BARCELLOS &amp; GRAZIA, 2003</bibRefCitation>
), being distinguished from the the former by the callus on corium and male genitalia, and from the latter by the yellowish apex of femora and base of tibiae.
</paragraph>
